      "name": "Mesh convergence study — three-level Richardson extrapolation",
      "description": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Grids of 2.1M, 6.8M, and 18.4M cells were evaluated. Grid convergence index (GCI) for the hemolysis index QoI was 3.2% on the medium grid and 1.1% on the fine grid, confirming acceptable discretization error at the selected resolution of 6.8M cells.",
