      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis bench validation against in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against in-vitro plasma-free hemoglobin measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. CFD predictions fell within ±18% of measured values at all operating points. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model was used with literature-derived exponent coefficients (α=0.785, β=0.062, C=1.8×10⁻⁶). Acceptance criterion RH < 1 was satisfied at all tested conditions.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
