      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Solver verification via method of manufactured solutions",
      "description": "The incompressible Navier-Stokes solver was verified against a manufactured solution for rotating-frame flow. Observed order of accuracy was 1.97 (theoretical: 2.0), confirming correct implementation of the finite-volume discretization and MRF rotating reference frame treatment. Residual convergence to 10⁻⁶ was achieved in all cases."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/vr/operating-condition-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Operating condition sensitivity sweep — 5 flow-speed combinations",
      "description": "CFD simulations were executed at flow rates of 2.5, 4.0, and 6.0 L/min combined with impeller speeds of 2000 and 3500 RPM. Worst-case hemolysis was identified at 2.5 L/min / 3500 RPM. Sensitivity of RH to ±5% variation in impeller tip clearance was quantified; RH varied by less than 8% across the geometric tolerance band, supporting robustness of the design acceptance conclusion.",
